Date: 28/12/1904
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 74
Edition:
Quote: Those present answered to their names, and at once preceded to draw lots for their places on the board, after which they got their shears, oil-stone, oil-rag, and water pot ready, so that they should be prepared to start when the bell rang for all aboard.
Notes:

